<p>Now,</p>
<p>\(\bar{x} = \frac{\sum fx}{N}\) = \(\frac{1800}{100}\) = 18</p>
<p>Standard deviation(σ) = \(\sqrt{\frac{\sum fx^2}{N} &#8211; \left ( \frac{\sum fx}{N} \right )^2}\)</p>
<p>= \(\sqrt{\frac{40100 }{100} &#8211; \left ( \frac{1800}{100} \right )^2}\)</p>
<p>= 8.77</p>
<p>And, Co-varience (c.v) = \(\frac{σ}{\bar{x}} \times 100%\)</p>
<p>= \(\frac{8.77}{18} \times 100%\)</p>
<p>= 48.72%</p>
