<p>Now,</p>
<p>\(\bar{x} = \frac{\sum fx}{N}\) = \(\frac{1700}{100}\) = 17</p>
<p>Standard deviation(σ) = \(\sqrt{\frac{\sum fx^2}{N} &#8211; \left ( \frac{\sum fx}{N} \right )^2}\)</p>
<p>= \(\sqrt{\frac{34000}{100} &#8211; \left ( \frac{1700}{100} \right )^2}\)</p>
<p>= 7.14</p>
<p>And, Co-varience (c.v) = \(\frac{σ}{\bar{x}} \times 100%\)</p>
<p>= \(\frac{7.14}{17} \times 100%\)</p>
<p>= 42%</p>
<p>Since, the standard deviation and covarience of company B is less than that of company A. so, company B is considered more consistent in terms of thickness of computer chip.</p>
