<td style="width: 20%; text-align: center;">Σx<sup>2</sup> = 22495</td>
<td style="width: 20%; text-align: center;">Σy<sup>2</sup> = 666509</td>
<td style="width: 20%; text-align: center;">Σxy = 118652</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Here, n = 8</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Part i)</span></p>
<p>We already assumed that the relationship between them is linear. The response variable is Y(Electric power).</p>
<p>Now, we know</p>
<p>The regression equation of y on x is</p>
<p>y = a + bx &#8212;&#8212;&#8211; (i)</p>
<p>The normal equation of Eqn(i) are</p>
<p>Σy = na + bΣx</p>
<p>2301 = 8a + 401b &#8212;&#8212;&#8211;(ii)</p>
<p>Also,</p>
<p>Σxy = aΣx + bΣx<sup>2</sup></p>
<p>118652 = 401a + 22495b  &#8212;&#8211;(iii)</p>
<p>Solving Equation (ii) and (iii), We get</p>
<p>\(\frac{\begin{matrix}287.625 \enspace =\enspace a \enspace +\enspace 50.125b\\295.891 \enspace =\enspace -a \enspace -\enspace 56.098b \end{matrix}}{-8.266 \enspace = \enspace -5.973b}\)</p>
<p>∴ b = 1.38</p>
<p>When, b = 1.38, we get</p>
<p>2301 = 8a + 401 x 1.38</p>
<p>a = 218.45</p>
<p>The final regression line is</p>
<p>y = a + bx</p>
<p>y = 218.45 + 1.38x</p>
